description.plain:
Omar Jeffery Pineiro (born May 15, 1997), known professionally as Smokepurpp, is an American rapper hailing from Miami-Dade County, Florida.

He was born in Chicago, Illinois, but his family moved to Florida when he was 3. He started as a producer and video editor before pursuing a rap career

His earliest songs on his SoundCloud date back to July 2015. Popular associated acts include Lil Pump, XXXTENTACION, and Ski Mask the Slump God.

In 2017 Smokepurpp was signed to Travis Scott’s record label, Cactus Jack Records, but left in 2019 for unknown reasons.

In 2019, Smokepurpp released his long awaited debut album Deadstar 2, the sequel to his 2017 mixtape Deadstar, with features from Denzel Curry, Trippie Redd, Ty Dolla $ign, Lil Skies, Moneybagg Yo, and Lil Pump.

songs.title: Audi.

description.plain: The prophecy Smokepurpp delivered on his late 2016 mixtape Up Now Fuck Next is coming true. Purpp debuts “Audi.,” a new track from his album DEADSTAR. Anchored by distorted bass and filled out with sonic flourishes that evoke the despair wrought by the plagues of Egypt, “Audi.” is about flexing on account of what Purpp already has built for himself, and ambition for his future plans.

songs.title: Nephew

description.plain:
“Nephew” is a bass-filled song by Smokepurpp and Lil Pump. They have collaborated frequently throughout their intertwined careers, including “Movin,” “OK,” and “Broke My Wrist.” The song was released on July 27, 2018.

Smokepurpp and Lil Pump both previously previewed “Nephew” on their respective Instagrams, and Smokepurpp played part of it during his set at Rolling Loud 2018.

The song was certified Gold by the RIAA on February 15, 2019.
